      "content": {
        "title": "Chemical Synapse Structure",
        "definition": "Specialized junction with presynaptic terminal containing vesicles, synaptic cleft, and postsynaptic membrane bearing neurotransmitter receptors.",
        "summary": "Synaptic structure determines transmission direction and specificity. The synaptic cleft separates pre- and postsynaptic membranes, preventing direct electrical coupling."
