        "definition": "Clostridial neurotoxins cleaving SNARE proteins: botulinum blocks presynaptic ACh release (flaccid paralysis); tetanus blocks inhibitory interneuron release (spastic paralysis).",
        "summary": "Both toxins are proteases targeting VAMP, SNAP-25, or syntaxin. Clinical presentations reflect affected synapse type."
